snippet.textDisplay:
Hi !
I feel like you don't have to worry (too much) about complications from what I hear the midwives usually have an ambulance on stand by to take you to the hospital + they are not going to let you do the home birth if they think you or the baby are in any kind of danger 😊
Don't put too much pressure on yourself -> again from what I heard from a few other mamas is that they planed to deliver their angel in a pool / bathtub and when the time came the didn't feel like it and went to do it on their bed or something ... -> the most important thing is that you feel safe and as much comfortable as you can 😊
Yes pregnancy brain is a thing 😊
Austin made me laugh so hard -> I remember when you showed him the video his mom made of one of your princesses coming out and he totally freaked out -> it's sweet that he wants to deliver your baby boy but if he can't stand the video I don't feel like he will when it will actually be real in front of him (with the blood and all) ...

snippet.textDisplay: I am about to have my second water birth. I would HIGHLY HIGHLY suggest it. I am on my 4th babe and my first 2 were hospital births, by FAR my 3rd was the fastest recovery and fastest labor out of all. I did a birthing tub but if you have a tub you are good to go. I would get some recommendations from some local moms on which midwife to go with and figure out who suits you best. Its so absolutely empowering to do it and i think you would be a great candidate. While you have some down time watch "Business of being born". Also homebirths are equally as safe as hospitals births, you obviously have to qualify ( it will depend on your midwife).
